No, the fatal attraction stalker is actually called the predatory stalker.

05:39.360 --> 05:42.250
They like to isolate or control their victims.

05:42.250 --> 05:46.320
Well, pretty much any stalker ghost would be creepy to me,

05:46.320 --> 05:48.690
so I could kind of understand shane was on a bender.

05:48.690 --> 05:52.600
You kn,ow in some twisted way, colleen actually believes she cares about shane,

05:52.600 --> 05:56.810
which means I have to convince her that the best thing for him is for her to move on.

05:56.810 --> 06:01.160
Well, if she really is a stalker, you know where to find her.

06:01.160 --> 06:04.860
And, uh, you know where to find me.

06:05.480 --> 06:08.670
I know you are not about to take that peanut butter up into my bed.

06:08.670 --> 06:10.430
Uh, no, no.

06:10.430 --> 06:14.270
I was gonna take this peanut butter up into my bed.

06:24.750 --> 06:26.820
Colleen calling...

06:49.720 --> 06:52.770
Stop it!

07:01.960 --> 07:03.940
Every monday...

07:03.940 --> 07:06.640
an orange rose.

07:06.640 --> 07:07.550
Don't forget.

07:07.550 --> 07:09.810
Colleen, I think you've got it wrong.

07:09.810 --> 07:10.750
You're confused.

07:10.750 --> 07:11.730
Shane is not your boyfriend.

07:11.730 --> 07:14.560
You have to send them every monday.

07:14.560 --> 07:17.370
You know, the best thing that you could do for shane is to go into the light.

07:17.370 --> 07:18.920
No.

07:18.920 --> 07:22.210
He needs to know how i felt.

07:26.320 --> 07:29.410
Well, I admit the night is pretty fuzzy, in fact,

07:29.410 --> 07:32.020
I'd kinda chalked it all up to being a drunken idiot,

07:32.020 --> 07:33.920
but I guess that's wishful thinking, isn't it?

07:33.920 --> 07:35.960
Yeah.

07:36.280 --> 07:39.680
I'm just gonna cut right to the chase.

07:40.250 --> 07:43.940
I see spirits, earthbound spirits,

07:43.940 --> 07:46.840
and I've seen colleen.

07:46.840 --> 07:48.830
So...

07:49.330 --> 07:51.770
you're telling me you see ghosts?

07:51.770 --> 07:54.500
I know that it's hard to believe.

07:55.130 --> 07:57.690
This is wild, but, um...

07:58.520 --> 08:00.380
well, I kinda knew it.

08:00.380 --> 08:02.860
Yeah, don't ask me how--

08:03.160 --> 08:04.700
hold on, wait, is she here right now?

08:04.700 --> 08:05.520
No.

08:05.520 --> 08:08.440
No, she was downstairs.

08:08.440 --> 08:12.540
She-- like the phone and the door?

08:12.540 --> 08:14.200
Wow, ok.

08:15.020 --> 08:17.040
At first I was little bit relieved, but now I'm kind of freaking out.

08:17.040 --> 08:18.340
You see, colleen, she was crazy.

08:18.340 --> 08:21.470
Ok, I don't think she wants to hurt you.

08:21.470 --> 08:23.430
If that helps you at all.

08:24.390 --> 08:29.000
she just needs to cross over into the light, and I can help her do that.

08:29.000 --> 08:31.140
Ok...

08:31.140 --> 08:32.950
uh, what I do until then?

08:32.950 --> 08:35.950
Once I get her to trust me, I might need you to talk to her.

08:35.950 --> 08:38.900
No, see, I don't-- I don't want to talk to her.

08:38.900 --> 08:40.350
She's warped.

08:40.350 --> 08:43.080
No, she had this big fantasy of us together.

08:43.080 --> 08:43.940
Couldn't let it go.

08:43.940 --> 08:48.090
She'd make up these insane stories, like trips we had supposedly been on,

08:48.090 --> 08:50.690
romantic dinners, even arguments we'd never had.

08:50.690 --> 08:53.210
Did you ever feel threatened?

08:53.210 --> 08:56.900
Well, it never quite got to where she was leaving dead rats on my doorstep,

08:56.900 --> 09:01.150
but, yeah, she was-- you know, she was sick, mentally--

09:01.150 --> 09:03.800
Hey, my lunch canceled, do you want to--oh.

09:03.800 --> 09:05.600
Excuse me.

09:05.600 --> 09:07.200
I see you've already made other plans.

09:07.200 --> 09:10.620
Uh, no, no, no, richard vaughn, this is melinda gordon.

09:10.620 --> 09:13.460
I met melinda and her husband last night.

09:13.460 --> 09:15.000
Oh, ha.

09:15.000 --> 09:16.300
My mistake.

09:16.300 --> 09:20.050
Just when I see a pretty woman in shane's office, I just assume.

09:20.050 --> 09:21.680
He's our resident heartbreaker.

09:21.680 --> 09:23.420
So I've heard.

09:23.420 --> 09:26.470
Uh, we had a mutual friend--colleen.

09:26.470 --> 09:27.940
Colleen?

09:27.940 --> 09:29.680
Oh, right, pretty intern.

09:29.680 --> 09:32.020
She was very nice, very nice.

09:32.020 --> 09:33.970
She had quite a thing for shane.

09:33.970 --> 09:37.910
Wasn't she the one that quit because he couldn't date interns?

09:37.910 --> 09:39.330
You're romanticizing again.

09:39.330 --> 09:42.200
She actually-- I think she just found a better gig.

09:42.200 --> 09:43.460
It was a pleasure meeting you.

09:43.460 --> 09:45.780
Nice to meet you.

09:49.340 --> 09:52.220
Ok, that was completely embarrassing.

09:52.220 --> 09:53.990
The fact is, I rarely go out.

09:53.990 --> 09:55.770
I'm up for partner, so I pretty much live here.

09:55.770 --> 09:58.130
Do you know how colleen died?

09:58.130 --> 10:00.880
I heard it was some kind of accident, but I'm not really sure.

10:00.880 --> 10:02.550
Well, what about friends?

10:02.550 --> 10:06.190
Family, an address, anything, even a last name?

10:06.190 --> 10:07.440
Finn.

10:07.440 --> 10:08.640
Colleen finn.

10:08.640 --> 10:10.780
But that really is pretty much all I've got.

10:10.780 --> 10:13.840
I mean, I can check to see if the firm kept any records on her.

10:13.840 --> 10:15.480
Ok.

10:15.480 --> 10:18.650
Well, if you come up with anything, um, please call me.

10:18.650 --> 10:20.460
Definitely.

10:20.460 --> 10:22.610
Look...

10:22.610 --> 10:27.520
whatever's going on here, I really need it to stop.

10:27.520 --> 10:29.940
Promise.

10:33.510 --> 10:34.940
Hey, what a nice surprise.

10:34.940 --> 10:36.500
Hi there.

10:36.500 --> 10:39.480
Somebody call for a handyman?

10:39.480 --> 10:42.270
I thought I'd check that circuit problem, being that,

10:42.270 --> 10:45.010
uh, delia might be minding the store on her own this weekend.

10:45.010 --> 10:47.450
That's right, your mom goes into surgery on friday.

10:47.450 --> 10:50.160
Tell me I can live in hope and tell her to leave us the keys to her apartment, right?

10:50.160 --> 10:50.970
It's doable.

10:50.970 --> 10:54.570
It would just be more doable if I could talk to someone who knew colleen.

10:54.570 --> 10:57.680
I can't even find out where she lived or worked, for that matter.

10:57.680 --> 10:58.740
Didn't you say she was an intern?

10:58.740 --> 11:00.650
Have you checked all the law firms in the area?

11:00.650 --> 11:03.380
Yeah, that and every florist within a 10 mile radius.

11:03.380 --> 11:06.600
I mean, she obviously paid cash for those flowers 'cause there was no record of her.

11:06.600 --> 11:08.690
I really am stumped.

11:08.690 --> 11:12.350
I've pretty much used up my quote of favors at the police station looking for your dad.

11:12.350 --> 11:15.440
Yeah, I know, but colleen has got to be on a police radar somehow.

11:15.440 --> 11:18.080
I mean, she was stalking someone, so...

11:18.080 --> 11:19.120
ask.

11:19.120 --> 11:22.670
I mean, if it, you know, means a weekend away, like this one.

11:22.670 --> 11:24.480
It does.I promise.

