What do you mean?

38:59.860 --> 39:02.630
She wasn't as alone as you thought she was.

39:02.630 --> 39:05.120
She had you.

39:05.120 --> 39:08.690
And you never stopped caring about her.

39:08.690 --> 39:13.800
Something tells me that, uh, that wasn't because of your job.

39:13.800 --> 39:16.180
That obvious, huh?

39:18.060 --> 39:22.010
Remind him of the time he walked me home from the station.

39:22.010 --> 39:25.760
He was telling me about his first arrest when he was a rookie.

39:25.760 --> 39:28.970
Do you remember the night that you walked her home?

39:28.970 --> 39:31.590
You were telling her about your first arrest.

39:31.590 --> 39:34.630
She told you that?

39:34.970 --> 39:37.300
It was just a purss natcher.

39:37.300 --> 39:43.080
I chased him into this lake and collared him about chest-deep in water.

39:43.080 --> 39:46.320
And for 2 weeks after that, you had flippers in your locker

39:46.320 --> 39:49.660
and wet wings on your desk.

39:49.660 --> 39:53.150
She laughed so hard.

39:53.600 --> 39:57.720
I hadn't seen her smile like that in a long time.

39:58.760 --> 40:02.920
I just remember wanting to freeze that moment.

40:02.920 --> 40:06.480
And then you got to her house?

40:06.480 --> 40:10.650
I was standing so close...

40:11.620 --> 40:14.210
and I just remember this--

40:14.210 --> 40:18.100
a strand of her hair fell on my face.

40:18.660 --> 40:22.370
I just didn't want to move.

40:25.160 --> 40:28.570
I just wanted to kiss her so bad.

40:28.570 --> 40:32.310
Took everything I had not to.

40:32.310 --> 40:35.530
She trusted me, so...

40:36.110 --> 40:39.370
I couldn'T.

40:40.010 --> 40:42.620
Did colleen really tell you all that?

40:42.620 --> 40:44.590
Yeah.

40:44.590 --> 40:50.210
She also told me that she wished you had kissed her.

41:08.790 --> 41:11.090
hey, wait.

41:12.150 --> 41:13.910
What just happened?

41:13.910 --> 41:16.140
Well, believe it or not...

41:17.400 --> 41:18.690
hey, what's up?

41:18.690 --> 41:19.970
I thought you had the day off.

41:19.970 --> 41:21.970
I just wanted to drop by and tell you the good news.

41:21.970 --> 41:24.360
Ned's application got accepted at the academy.

41:24.360 --> 41:27.360
So how did you undo all the damage that shane caused?

41:27.360 --> 41:30.210
It wasn't easy, but we had his real school counselor call

41:30.210 --> 41:32.970
and just tell them it was a prank.

41:32.970 --> 41:36.180
I am so sorry that you got caught up in all this.

41:37.400 --> 41:38.780
What happened to that creep?

41:38.780 --> 41:42.060
Well, he got fired from his job, the county is pressing charges,

41:42.060 --> 41:45.090
he's out on bail, my guess is he's somewhere laying low,

41:45.090 --> 41:48.240
and jim is walking me home from work every night.

41:48.240 --> 41:50.880
That is so crazy.

41:50.880 --> 41:53.130
Well, I will see you tomorrow.

41:53.130 --> 41:55.260
I have more errands to run.

41:55.260 --> 41:57.090
You know what, I didn't bring those sconces up,

41:57.090 --> 41:58.830
because that basement is dead to me.

41:58.830 --> 42:00.600
All those lights just shorted out again.

42:00.600 --> 42:01.360
Ok.

42:01.360 --> 42:03.330
Bye.

42:05.220 --> 42:07.510
Jim just fixed that!

42:07.510 --> 42:09.890
Yeah, I'm looking for it right now.

42:11.020 --> 42:14.290
Ugh, I'll call you back, delia.

42:15.790 --> 42:19.050
Miss me?

42:21.140 --> 42:22.640
This is my husband.

42:22.640 --> 42:25.330
Like I care.

42:25.890 --> 42:28.620
Jim: Melinda, you're not gonna believe this, but--

42:28.620 --> 42:30.530
shane's dead, right?

42:30.530 --> 42:31.930
Yeah, oded.Pills, booze.

42:31.930 --> 42:33.910
We just got the call.How did you know?

42:33.910 --> 42:35.480
Because he's right here.

42:35.480 --> 42:37.390
Mel, get away from him, now!

42:37.390 --> 42:38.640
Melinda?

42:38.640 --> 42:39.380
Melinda!

42:39.380 --> 42:41.850
This worked out the best all around.

42:41.850 --> 42:43.770
Don't you think?

42:43.770 --> 42:46.400
Now we can be together.

42:46.400 --> 42:49.500
Forever.

